# Search Before Adding

- Before adding a new function, class, module, or utility: search the codebase for existing implementations or similar patterns (e.g. same domain, same API shape).
- Reuse or extend existing code rather than duplicating. If you are unsure, spend extra time searching (e.g. `grep`, codebase search) before writing new code.
- This applies to both Rust and frontend (TypeScript/Svelte) code.
